definition.value: A secondary carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methyl-1H-pyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 2-[2,4-bis(trifluoromethyl)phenoxy]aniline. It is a fungicide developed by Shandong United Pesticide Industry Co. that demonstrates effective control against soybean rust, corn rust, and wheat powdery mildew.

A benzamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-{[(2,2-difluoro-1,3-benzodioxol-5-yl)carbonyl](methyl)amino}-2-fluorobenzoic acid with the amino group of 2-bromo-6-(difluoromethoxy)-4-(1,1,1,2,3,3,3-heptafluoropropan-2-yl)aniline. It is an insecticide developed by Jiangsu Yangnong Chemical Co., Ltd.
An organic cation that is the conjugate acid of ambiguine H resulting from the protonation of the isocyano group; Major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A member of the class of quinazolines that is 1-methylquinazoline-2,4(1H,3H)-dione substituted by 3-chlorophenyl, methyl, and {5-[(diethylcarbamoyl)oxy]-1,3-dimethyl-1H-pyrazol-4-yl}carbonyl groups at positions 3, 5, and 6, respectively. It is a herbicide developed by Liaoning Cynda Chemical Co. Ltd.
A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of etherolenic acid resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group; Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Any sesquiterpene having a cadinane skeleton containing one or more C=C bonds.

A member of the class of pyridines that is pyridine substituted by 2-[(1E)-1,3-dimethoxy-3-oxoprop-1-en-2-yl]phenoxy and trifluoromethyl groups at positions 2 and 4, respectively. It is an insecticide developed by Syngenta Crop Protection AG.

A member of the class of indazoles that is 2H-indazole substituted by pyridin-3-yl and N-(1-methylcyclopropyl)aminoacyl groups at positions 2 and 4, respectively. It is an insecticide developed by FMC Corp.

A member of the class of triazoles that is 1H-1,2,4-triazole substituted by (1E)-3-amino-3-oxo-2-(pyrimidin-5-yl)prop-1-en-1-yl and 3,5-bis(trifluoromethyl)phenyl groups at positions 1 and 3, respectively. It is a second-generation exportin 1 inhibitor that is currently in phase II clinical trial for the treatment of patients with higher relapsed/refractory myelodysplastic neoplasms.
Any inhibitor of exportin 1.

A member of the class of triazoles that is 1H-1,2,4-triazole substituted by (1Z)-3-oxo-3-[2-(pyrazin-2-yl)hydrazinyl]prop-1-en-1-yl and 3,5-bis(trifluoromethyl)phenyl groups at positions 1 and 3, respectively. It is a prescription medicine approved for the treatment of adult patients with relapsed or refractory diffuse large B-cell lymphoma.

A member of the class of triazoles that is 1H-1,2,4-triazole substituted by (1E)-3-amino-2-{4-[(methylsulfonyl)amino]phenyl}-3-oxoprop-1-en-1-yl and 3,5-bis(trifluoromethyl)phenyl groups at positions 1 and 3, respectively. It is an exportin 1 inhibitor.

A methoxy-1,3,5-triazine that is 1,3,5-triazine substituted by 2-{[(difluoromethyl)sulfonyl](methyl)amino}-3-fluorobenzoyl, methoxy and methoxy groups at positions 2, 4, and 6, respectively. It is a herbicide developed by Bayer CropScience AG for weed control in rice and its mode of action is inhibition of the enzyme acetolactate synthase.
An N-sulfonylurea that is N-carbamoyl-2-iodobenzenesulfonamide bearing a 4-methoxy-6-methyl-1,3,5-triazin-2-yl substituent at position N3.
An organic anion that is the conjugate base of iofensulfuron resulting from the deprotonation of the N-sulfonylurea moiety: Major species at pH 7.3.
The organic sodium salt of iofensulfuron. It is a cross-spectrum herbicide developed by Bayer for use in cereals, corn, soybeans, rice, turf and non-crops.
A cyclohexenecarboxylic acid that is 4-oxocyclohexanecarboxylic acid carrying a double bond at position 2.
Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the amino group of pre-putrebactin; Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A tautomer resulting from the transfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the amino group of bisucaberin B; Major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A diester resulting from the formal condensation of the two hydroxy groups of 3-fluorocatechol with the carboxy groups of 3-hydroxybenzoic acid. It is an inhibitor of glucose transporter 1 (GLUT1) that suppresses tumour growth in mouse xenograft models.
Any substance that inhibits the action of glucose transporters.
Any glucose transporter inhibitor that interferes with the action of glucose transporter 1.
Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
